A science teacher at Retief High Schools in the Free State sweeps Rinkhals out of his class (eNCA/Screenshot) JOHANNESBURG - Teachers get to see a lot of charachters in the classroom. However, a Free State teacher got a little more than he bargained for. A video shows Science teacher, Christo, using a broom to sweep a rinkhals out of his class. READ: Free State pushing hard to vaccinate teachers The Retief High School teacher says he was writing on the board when he spotted something strange moving on the ground. In the video, frantic pupils could be seen screaming from the top of their desks. His quick thinking averted a potential disaster as rinkhals can spit toxic venom up to 3 metres. Once outside, the snake was humanely captured and released nearby. A video shows a science teacher, Christo, using a broom to sweep a rinkhals out of his class. #eNCA’s @HeidiGiokos brings you more on this. #AllAngles #DStv403 pic.twitter.com/4pSDFxGW4j